</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="selectedRows-method">
<db:title>QModelIndexList selectedRows(int <db:emphasis>column</db:emphasis>)</db:title>
<db:para>Returns the indexes in the given <db:code role="parameter">column</db:code> for the rows where all columns are selected.</db:para>
<db:section>
<db:title>See Also</db:title>
<db:para><db:emphasis>See also </db:emphasis>
<db:simplelist type="vert" role="see-also">
<db:member><db:link xlink:href="qml-qtqml-models-itemselectionmodel.xml#selectedColumns-method">selectedColumns</db:link>()</db:member>
</db:simplelist>
</db:para>
</db:section>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="setCurrentIndex-method">
<db:title>void setCurrentIndex(QModelIndex <db:emphasis>index</db:emphasis>, SelectionFlags <db:emphasis>command</db:emphasis>)</db:title>
<db:para>Sets the model item <db:code role="parameter">index</db:code> to be the current item, and emits <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtqml-models-itemselectionmodel.xml#currentChanged-signal">currentChanged</db:link>(). The current item is used for keyboard navigation and focus indication; it is independent of any selected items, although a selected item can also be the current item.</db:para>
<db:para>Depending on the specified <db:code role="parameter">command</db:code>, the <db:code role="parameter">index</db:code> can also become part of the current selection.</db:para>
<db:para>Valid <db:code role="parameter">command</db:code> values are described in <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtqml-models-itemselectionmodel.xml#select-method">select(<db:emphasis>index</db:emphasis>, <db:emphasis>command</db:emphasis>)</db:link>.</db:para>
<db:section>
<db:title>See Also</db:title>
<db:para><db:emphasis>See also </db:emphasis>
<db:simplelist type="vert" role="see-also">
<db:member><db:link xlink:href="qml-qtqml-models-itemselectionmodel.xml#select-method">select</db:link>()</db:member>
</db:simplelist>
</db:para>
</db:section>
